name: 16-methyl-17-oxoandrost-5-en-3-yl acetate
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-3550
Reason: 16-methyl-17-oxoandrost-5-en-3-yl acetate is a steroid-like compound with a melting point that needs to be predicted. We will use the melting point of cholesterol as a reference, as it is a related steroid with a well-known melting point of 130°C (according to the CRC Handbook of Chemistry and Physics, 49th Edition, 1968-1969). We will consider the functional group effects on the melting point, such as the methyl group, which can increase the melting point by around +30 to +50°C, and the oxo group, which can contribute around +20 to +40°C. Additionally, we will consider the effect of the acetate group, which can reduce the melting point by around -20 to -40°C.
